\end_inset

Calcoliamo i prodotti tra gli elementi di ciascuna 
\emph on
antidiagonale
\emph default
 e sommiamoli tra loro:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\textcolor{red}{\ensuremath{a_{11}}}\cdot\textcolor{red}{\ensuremath{a_{23}}}\cdot\textcolor{red}{\ensuremath{a_{32}}}+\textcolor{blue}{\ensuremath{a_{12}}}\cdot\textcolor{blue}{\ensuremath{a_{21}}}\cdot\textcolor{blue}{\ensuremath{a_{33}}}+\textcolor{violet}{\ensuremath{a_{13}}}\cdot\textcolor{violet}{\ensuremath{a_{22}}}\cdot\textcolor{violet}{\ensuremath{a_{31}}}
\]

\end_inset


\series bold
Sottraiamo 
\series default
alla 
\emph on
somma dei prodotti delle diagonali
\emph default
,
 
\emph on
la somma dei prodotti delle antidiagonali
\emph default
:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\textcolor{magenta}{\ensuremath{a_{11}}}\cdot\textcolor{magenta}{\ensuremath{a_{22}}}\cdot\textcolor{magenta}{\ensuremath{a_{33}}}+\textcolor{green}{\ensuremath{a_{12}}}\cdot\textcolor{green}{\ensuremath{a_{23}}}\cdot\textcolor{green}{\ensuremath{a_{31}}}+\textcolor{orange}{\ensuremath{a_{13}}}\cdot\textcolor{orange}{\ensuremath{a_{21}}}\cdot\textcolor{orange}{\ensuremath{a_{32}}}-(\textcolor{red}{\ensuremath{a_{11}}}\cdot\textcolor{red}{\ensuremath{a_{23}}}\cdot\textcolor{red}{\ensuremath{a_{32}}}+\textcolor{blue}{\ensuremath{a_{12}}}\cdot\textcolor{blue}{\ensuremath{a_{21}}}\cdot\textcolor{blue}{\ensuremath{a_{33}}}+\textcolor{violet}{\ensuremath{a_{13}}}\cdot\textcolor{violet}{\ensuremath{a_{22}}}\cdot\textcolor{violet}{\ensuremath{a_{31}}})
\]

\end_inset


\series bold
Il determinante 
\begin_inset Formula $\textrm{det}(A)$
\end_inset

 è quindi:
\series default

\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\textrm{det}(A)=\textcolor{magenta}{\ensuremath{a_{11}}}\cdot\textcolor{magenta}{\ensuremath{a_{22}}}\cdot\textcolor{magenta}{\ensuremath{a_{33}}}+\textcolor{green}{\ensuremath{a_{12}}}\cdot\textcolor{green}{\ensuremath{a_{23}}}\cdot\textcolor{green}{\ensuremath{a_{31}}}+\textcolor{orange}{\ensuremath{a_{13}}}\cdot\textcolor{orange}{\ensuremath{a_{21}}}\cdot\textcolor{orange}{\ensuremath{a_{32}}}-\textcolor{red}{\ensuremath{a_{11}}}\cdot\textcolor{red}{\ensuremath{a_{23}}}\cdot\textcolor{red}{\ensuremath{a_{32}}}-\textcolor{blue}{\ensuremath{a_{12}}}\cdot\textcolor{blue}{\ensuremath{a_{21}}}\cdot\textcolor{blue}{\ensuremath{a_{33}}}-\textcolor{violet}{\ensuremath{a_{13}}}\cdot\textcolor{violet}{\ensuremath{a_{22}}}\cdot\textcolor{violet}{\ensuremath{a_{31}}}
\]

\end_inset


\series bold
NOTA
\series default
:
 
\emph on
È possibile ricopiare la matrice una sola volta e tracciare le diagonali e le antidiagonali direttamente.
 È anche possibile utilizzare direttamente le formule senza rappresentarle graficamente.
 
