\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\text{dim}(\text{Ker}(L_{A}))+\text{dim}(\text{Im}(L_{A}))=n
\]

\end_inset

Si trasforma in:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\text{dim}(S_{0})+\text{dim}(\text{rk}(A))=n
\]

\end_inset

Riordinando abbiamo:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\text{dim}(S_{0})=n-\text{dim}(\text{rk}(A))
\]

